Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In September I gave a kidney (1000 points). In March I had a shoot-out with rival gang lords on the 5 near LA (-76 points). Last Friday I signed my organ donor card (28 points). In October I gave a life-saving blood transfusion (50 points). In May I helped see the light (8 points).

Overall, I've been nice (1010 points). For Christmas I deserve a Lego set!

Sincerely,
magic_264

Write your letter to Santa! Enter your LJ username:

As of today, It has been 1 year since I moved to Kamloops. I wore black today.

I also went to Logan Lake, out for lunch with aunty rosanne and uncle mike to Milestones, because they are leaving tomorrow, and then out to Knouff lake, which is up by Sun Peaks I think. And then I found a geocache. Then came home and have been studying since. But Jamie cullum is haunting me again. Particularly, "twentysomething" which is about how you study your ass off and then all of a sudden you find yourself a twentysomething with no real point... you could work, you could fall in love, maybe that will solve all your problems, but you don't know dick about "love". you have all this anticipation and wonder, but you realize that "the world don't need scholars as much as I thought" He even mentions how being an expert on Shakespeare may SEEM like a great accomplishment, but that doesn't mean you'll be happy or content or anyone in the real world cares. screw it, you can read the lyrics yourself.


After years of expensive education
A car full of books and anticipation
I'm an expert on Shakespeare and that's a hell of a lot
But the world don't need scholars as much as I thought
Maybe I'll go travelling for a year
Finding myself, or start a career
Could work the poor, though I'm hungry for fame
We all seem so different but we're just the same
Maybe I'll go to the gym, so I don't get fat
Aren't things more easy, with a tight six pack
Who knows the answers, who do you trust
I can't even separate love from lust
Maybe I'll move back home and pay off my loans
Working nine to five, answering phones
But don't make me live for Friday nights
Drinking eight pints and getting in fights
Maybe I'll just fall in love
That could solve it all
Philosophers say that that's enough
There surely must be more
Love ain't the answer, nor is work
The truth eludes me so much it hurts
But I'm still having fun and I guess that's the key
I'm a twentysomething and I'll keep being me

I'm so not tired right now. I should be. Stupid early-morning waking up habits. I don't know how many times I woke up this morning thinking "ergh, time to get ready for work, need to catch my bus... wait, what time is it? only 4, I can go back to sleep for another 4 hours"
I don't have any good books to read right now either. I have one, but it is a little too smart for my current state. and there are a couple I want to start, but they are both giant hardcovers, which are such a pain in the bum, as far as carrying them around, or leaving them on my pillow when I sleep. 
Over all, things are going quite well in my life. I totally don't want to move back to kamloops, but just when I start to think "maybe I could take the year off school, switch to uvic..." I go and look at my classes in all their psych (and english minor) glory, and I get all geeky excited. But theres like, a billion things I want to do here before I go back. I've found 97 geocaches.. I am super excited about making it to 100! I know I've found at least that many, but haven't logged them all. It is just a number, a stat, but still, it will be cool.
Kristi is back! yay!
what else... hmm... I don't know. Maybe I'll just go watch my illegally downloaded TV for a while, and hope I fall asleep to that. Or stay up really late and worry about whatever new prognosis House comes up with. 
good night

Update:
things are all fantastic. Well, as far as I'm concerned. Having fun, surviving on my own (despite what many people projected) have an ok-place (ghetto, but not like, health-concern ghetto), a fun job...

now that that is over with, here is a picture of kergin in ugly pants, standing next to Lindsay Lohan.

Update, because I don't have much to do. Well, I do, but nothing fun today. And nothing concrete and productive. 
Soo... yeah. Moved back to Victoria for the summer. And finally I'm here, with all my stuff, after a few special little trials. 
I'm looking for a place to live, and consequently a job. Although I don't want to get a job until I know where abouts I'm going to live. And I've found a few places to live. The one place we really like is across the road from Lisa's place, pretty much. Like, a 1 minute walk. And the people are super nice, all utilities included, on nice bus routes, a nice neighborhood, fairly ccentral location. Our 2nd choice is in the quadra mcKenzie area, which is cheaper, but smaller, no internet, and no washer/dryer. On a bus route, but not so nice, and fairly out of the way. It would be different if one of us was going to school. 
So really, I have no idea whats going on. I really should be spazzing and freaking out and snapping because of my lack of direction and no control over the situation, but I'm not. Which is actually really nice. I think I just MAY have loosened up a bit! Thats what I'm most proud of. And its not even that I'm "handling it well", I just really don't mind too much. 
In the mean time I'm staying at Lisas... we're getting along fine.. the only time shes ever really home is when shes sleeping, shes either at work or at her barn, sometimes out with her boyfriend. So I cook and clean and terrorize the cat. Play some computer, go for walks, reading a lot... its a rough life, but I'm adapting. 
It is great to be back in Victoria, doing stuff. Where there is actually stuff to do! You can't really just go "out" in kamloops... you can't really wander around downtown, randomly stopping here or there, going in the different stores, watching street performers, visiting the waterfront or seals or whatever else. 
My personal life is also not going exactly according to my plans, and perhaps for the best. Again, I'm just kind of going along with things, trying not to freak out about it, enjoy what I can. So far so good. I'm starting to figure out that when I try too hard, things never work out. So hopefully when I just let things go, things will all work out nicely!

Also, my birthday soon. I am not quite sure whats going on with that, but I want to go out dancing! Hopefully saturday.

A lot of them I'm sure a lot of you have already seen. I intend to add more, but I don't have the motivation tonight.

alright, another sort-of semester down. I have 2 exams to go, but I'm not worried. I have study groups set up for both of them, which I am looking forward too.. I haven't had a study group in like, a year! Carla, you're probably the only one who will understand :)
I dyed Easter eggs tonight! I'll try to post pictures tomorrow... we made a giant mess. We also made a cake, with like, 4 different types of sprinkles, mini m&ms, animal crackers, rocket candies... I think I'm missing something, but thats ok. yeah, good cake! and my easter eggs consist of a scottsman, a pirate, rainbow, squares... I can't think of the others. I have to post pictures. And kristi made the ninja turtles! So cool!
And my aunt, uncle, and cousins staying with me bought me a better video card (or whatever it was that my computer was lacking) for sharing my space and giving up my nice big bed, so  now I can play WoW on my computer, which is just trouble :) This also means my mom is probably going to buy me oblivion for my birthday. yay!
I'm just really optimistic right now, a lot of stuff to look forward to this summer, a lot of people I am looking forward to seeing again. Granted, that usually means there is a lot of room for disapointment and failed plans, but thats ok. Things even look good in Kamloops for the next little while. But maybe thats just because I know I am leaving ;)
I really should be going to bed, I work fairly early tomorrow. 
Moser out!

Ohmyfuckinggod I hate my film teacher so much. Aside from the fact that he's uber condescending, insulting, cuts off his students when they are talking/asking questions, hasn't actually taught us anything, and expects far too much from first year students, he assigned a $120 text book, and told us last night that it was a waste of money, because we won't need it for the class. HE TOLD US TO BUY IT THE FIRST WEEK! AND WE KEPT ASKING HIM "should we be doing some readings or anything?" "oh, no, not yet" he would reply. FUCKING BULLSHIT! Didn't ever even assign it for background info, or anything! In most classes you're at least supposed to be following along with the text throughout the class, even if it is just supplementary, and not testable or anything like that. I'm pretty sure mose teachers don't expect you to actually read it, except PERHAPS right before the test. But to not even use it for that??? and it would be one thing if it was like, a $40 text. or they had them used. or they could be in the book buy-back. But $120! and since they change the topic of the film class every time they teach it, it can't be bought back. And it was REQUIRED! there was an optional book, too, for an extra $40 that some kids bought, that is also not applicable or useful at all. 

And because I am trying to be less whiny and negative, I will end on a good note.
I love dusk... It is probably even cooler than any old cliche sunset. It has a spooky, mystical essence to it. And it plays tricks with your eyes, and your mind, because you have no sense of what colours things are supposed to be.. and the street lights are all kind of on, but they aren't really sure what the hell is going on either, because they look like they shouldn't be on, because there is still light, but then if they went off then it would be too dark... and this crazy sensation and confusion only lasts like, 5 minutes. but at the same time it is rather settling, cozy, calming... and its just not the same if you are inside, looking out. You have to be out in the middle of dusk, experiencing it. 
Hardly poetic, but there you go.

First and foremost:
Happy steak and blowjob day! Congrats to everyone who has someone special to share this day with!

They have screwed around with the rich textness of LJ. So this might get a little messed up. Or I might get carried away. We'll see.

Other than that, I don't really have much to say. I suppose I could do a quick whats-going-on-in-my-life update, but I don't think anyone here really cares who doesn't already know. And not much is new anyways. Ah, well, what the hell.

School is good, in the middle of another batch of midtermy goodness and papers. there is only like, 5 weeks left, give or take, and in that time I have 3 finals, 2 papers, and 1 presentation. Managable.
It turns out that I can't go to England (or australia) for school next year, as I was told at the last minute that I wouldn't be able to, due to my lack of a second language, that I'm supposed to be taking in my 3rd year. well, actually, I'm supposed to be taking it in my first or 2nd year, but that didn't happen. And it is a TRU thing, not a psych thing. Which of course broke my heart because I was already like, luggage shopping pretty much. went through a lovely few days of sulking and not talking to anyone and not eating. Then into a worse stage and bitchiness and eating everything in sight. Ok, it wasn't that bad. But I was crushed.
Work is fine... out of the 10 people in electronics, we're losing 3 within the next 4 weeks. 1 is already gone. and my boss is a jerk. and people are stupid. and customers make stuff up just to bug me. But I got a Harry Potter T-shirt! and a spokes-cowboy came in this week to promote Walk the Line, and he gave me a free poster and signed it. He was awesome! He'd pose, and tip his hat at all the ladies...  But then he had to leave because he was late for his anime club meeting. so cute and dweeby! what a man! (no, I dont want to get with the wal mart spokes-cowboy. He just amused me, is all).

So, I'm studying for my stats midterm (which is in less than 22 hours), and I come across this guy, William Gosset, who worked for Guiness breweries back int eh early 1900's, and how his love of barley and brewing inspired him to come up with the t-distribution, and a bunch of other important psych statistical concepts. Not to mention how much he must have contributed to the world of guiness! Personally, barley has never inspired me too much...

you can tell I'm avoiding studying, with all the rambling I'm doing. Maybe its all the pink floyd I've been listening to... they kinda seem to just spit out random words in a nice little sing-song way, with little meaning or relevence.
The lunatic is in my head
The lunatic is in my head
You raise the blade, you make the change
you re-arrange me till I'm sane
 Sorry if that offends any pink floyd fans in the crowd. Yay for drug use! It reminds me of my english class the other night... the teacher lectured for an hour on how our generation has it all wrong, that we use drugs for fun, not to expand our minds and reach enlightenment, which is what they should be for. We are shallow with our drug use, when it could be such an enriching experience. we're missing out. Then she went on to say that we were all stupid for going to school, and being arts students, because thats not the way to become successful and complete the american dream, and we are failing at life, in a way. Granted, we all know thats true, and it is not her way to sugar-coat things, but she doesn't need to be so tactless and explicit! and we all just laughed, because we know its true.

I can't wait until next year, when I can actually get back to studying real psych... for the past 2 fucking years I've been taking "biopsych" and "psych stats" and "psych research methods" and "the history of psych", I miss studying actual people! Thats the part I love so much! I don't care their behaviour is within 2 standard deviations of the population mean, I care that they are doing it! "and how does this make you feel?" Soon enough...!

we got a couple new foster kids yesterday. a 14 month old, and a 4 year old. Not bad (yet), but annoying. Especially when I'm studying for a midterm. Maybe they will settle down. Or maybe I will warm up to them. But they will be here for like, 3 months, so I suppose I should get used to it. Or move out. hey! now theres an idea...

And just to make this post EXTRA long and annoying, here are the lyrics for the song I am currently listening to!:

THE JUICE OF THE BARLEY
In the sweet country Lim'rick, one cold winter's night
All the turf fires were burning when I first saw the light;
And a drunken old midwife went tipsy with joy
As she danced round the floor with her slip of a boy,

Singing ban-ya-na mo if an-ga-na
And the juice of the barley for me.

Well when I was a gossoon of eight years old or so
With me turf and me primer to school I did go.
To a dusty old school house without any door,
 Where lay the school master blind drunk on the floor,

At the learning I wasn't such a genius I'm thinking,
But I soon bet the master entirely at drinking,
Not a wake or a wedding for five miles around,
But meself in the corner was sure to be found.

One Sunday the priest thread me out from the altar
Saying you'll end up your days with your neck in a halter;
And you'll dance a fine jig between heaven and hell A
nd his words they did frighten me the truth for to tell,

So the very next morning as the dawn it did break
I went down to the vestry the pledge for to take,
And there in that room sat the priests in a bunch
Round a big roaring fire drinking tumblers of punch,

Well from that day to this I have wandered alone
I'm a jack of all trades and a master of none,
With the sky for me roof and the earth for me floor,
And I'll dance out my days frinking whiskey galore,

This morning I woke up and had this horrible realization that I was supposed to write a paper for my history class over reading break, and I didn't. THEN I realized that I'm not taking a history class... and I don't have any papers or assignments due any time soon. Well, my transfer application. And a film midterm. but I am well aware of both of those.
WtF?
I can only assume I was having a nutty dream that I don't remember.

wow, I had so much fun in Victoria! lunches at moxies, irish times, cafe mexico, Sounds like coffee! Seeing GOOD strippers! Hiking and caching and swimming! going to the movies, and renting movies! Playing at the beach! Running into old friends (and parents of old friends)! And a fair amount of drinking! And I think I drank more coffee, and met more people, in the one week I was there than I have in the past month! And I seemed to have developed a thing for exclamation marks!
Also, I'm pretty sure I managed to keep myself more or less out of trouble! I pretty much know where I stand with everyone I interacted with, with no ugliness! (well, maybe still a bit of ugliness with Jim, but at least I made the effort to say hi!) Which is an achievement for little mouthy, judgemental, emotional me!
There are of course a couple people I missed out on the hanging out with. Hopefully I'll be back soon enough! You know who you are, and know that I feel bad for not seeing you!
also, I didn't get to go to Mr. Tubbs. Or goldstream. or stock up on my soap candy stock, although they might sell them here at Zack's candy shop, but its a matter of getting downtown to pick some up.
thanks to everyone (who actually reads this) that I saw in Victoria for entertaining me! I miss you all!

Home hasn't changed. my parents are still nutty, its still smelly and cold here. My keyboard isn't working very well, which is new. 

Kristi came over last night and we made <strike> a huge-ass ginormous mess </strike>  apple crisps. Good times! And they are actually tastey!

quick update that I have to share with someone.
I was at the mall today, because I need new shoes (yes, NEED, but no, I didn't find any. although I did buy a cute new purse!), and I saw these 2 girls, like, 17 years old, dressed all trendy-like. and they were wearing matching newsboy or poorboy caps or whatever. in silver. first of all, it was stupid because they had them pulled down so low they had to tilt their heads way back to look at each other when they were talking, but secondly, and most importantly, THEY BOTH LOOKED LIKE THEY HAD A COOKED THING OF JIFFY POP ON THEIR HEADS! it was so amusing!
 , for example. Their's were a lot shinier, though. I didn't get a picture, but it brightened up my day.
Ok, back to doing my english paper, which I hate. And studying for stats, which I hate more. And I have some reading I have to do for film, too, which I may or may not get around to doing.
Happy Birthday, B-short!

The little bastard saw his shadow- more winter.

But I hope you all have a happy groundhog day, filled with love and happiness, family, fertility, prosperity, good fortune, longevity, national pride, and everything else groundhog day stands for!
Or maybe I need to do some research on what groundhog day stands for. But really, why shouldn't you have all those things?

• The zone phone has been amusing me lately
  • I got to give kristi a hair cut last weekend! And shes still talking to me! It was fun! Now I can say "psh, yeah, of course I've cut hair before!"
  • I trimmed my bangs with scrap booking / crinkle-cut scissors, because thats all I could find and they were bugging me.
  • I need a haircut. I was going to wait until my trip to Victoria on reading break, but...
  • I don't think I'm going to get time off to go to Victoria on reading break. My boss is a jerk, and he SOOOO could have given me the time off, but he's just too lazy. Oh well, I'll see all you Victorians in May I guess.
  • I hate all my teachers right now.
    • I hate my film teacher because he won't give clear expectations or boundries for our essay topics. Just that we need one, that relates to the class. But he hasn't actually taught us anything, and seems to be making it up as he goes along.
    • I hate my english teacher because she gave us explicit topics for our essays, but I've picked 2 of them so far and shes shot down both.
    • I hate my stats teacher because I have a stats midterm next week, and he's sick, canceling not only class, but his office hours too. And I had an appointment to see him and everything, and he STILL got sick, knowing full well that I wanted to see him. jerk!
  • I've been cold all day, so I think I will have  nice long bath now. 
  • I was supposed to be hanging out with Tria tonight, but we didn't call each other. again.
  • This day in history: 1814 "The Corsair" by Lord Byron is published

From Wikipedia, for anyone who was wondering how big Kamloops is:

Kamloops is a city in central British Columbia, Canada at the confluence of the two branches of the Thompson River and on the shore of Kamloops Lake. It is the seat of the Thompson-Nicola Regional District. Kamloops is also the "Tournament Capital of Canada".

History
The Kamloops area was inhabited by the Secwepemc (Shuswap) nation (part of the Salishan speaking people) prior to the arrival of European settlers. The first European explorers arrived in 1811, and a fur trading post was established by David Stuart in 1812 for the Pacific Fur Company. This was bought out by the North West Company shortly after, and by 1821, the Hudson's Bay Company had control of the fur trade in Kamloops.

The gold rush of the 1850's and the construction of the Canadian Pacific Railway in the 1880s brought further growth, resulting in the City of Kamloops being incorporated in 1893 with a population of about 500.

"Kamloops" is the anglicized version of the Shuswap word "Tk'emlups", meaning 'where the rivers meet'. Shuswap is still actively spoken in the area by members of the Kamloops Indian Band.

Industry
Major Kamloops-area industries include primary resource processing (pulp mill, copper mine, ranching) as well as tertiary services (provincial lottery headquarters). Kamloops is also a transportation hub for the region, with three major highways, and a semi-international airport.

Climate
While situated in a semi-arid desert valley, Kamloops winters are generally mild with an occasional cold snap. Snow is common from December to March. Winter mean minimun temperature of -6.1'C and peak around -30'C. On the other hand, summers in Kamloops can be quite hot. Temperatures of above 40'C have been recorded.

Demographics
(according to Statistics Canada 2001 census)
Population: 77,281.
Growth Rate (1996-2001): 1.2%
Total Private Dwellings: 32,076
Area: 297.57 km2
Density: 259.7 people per km2
